== Markets ==
=== Japan ===
The Japanese market-spec bZ4X was announced in April 2022 and launched on 12 May 2022. The model is only available for lease through the company's Kinto service to "eliminate customer concerns" regarding battery electric vehicle while "taking the environment into consideration".<ref name=bZ4X-PR />

In the first phase, up to 3,000 lease applications will be accepted starting from 12 May; a second phase will follow in fall 2022, and Toyota/Kinto plan to lease up to 5,000 vehicles per year thereafter.<ref name=Kinto-lease>{{cite news |url=https://car.watch.impress.co.jp/docs/news/1406960.html |title=トヨタ、新型バッテリEV「bZ4X」のKINTO月額利用料を決定 最初の4年は補助金適用で8万8220円から |language=ja |trans-title=Toyota announces KINTO monthly lease fees for new battery EV 'bZ4X': From 88,220 yen for the first 4 years with applied subsidy |author=小林 隆 |date=May 2, 2022 |work=Car Watch |access-date=3 May 2022}}</ref>

The bZ4X is available in one grade, Z, with front-wheel drive and all-wheel drive options.<ref name=bZ4X-PR>{{Cite web |date=2022-04-12 |title=Toyota to Launch All-New bZ4X BEV on May 12 in Japan |url=https://global.toyota/en/newsroom/toyota/37135919.html |access-date=2022-04-25 |website=Toyota Motor Corporation Official Global Website |language=en}}</ref> Specific packages include a choice of roof (standard or panoramic moon roof) and wheel size (18- or 20-inch diameter). The car is available with one of two interior colours and one of eleven exterior colours.<ref name=4-goals>{{cite news |url=https://car.watch.impress.co.jp/docs/news/1402312.html |title=トヨタ、新型バッテリEV「bZ4X」詳報 開発時に掲げた4つの目標価値とは |language=ja |trans-title=Detailed report for Toyota's new battery EV 'bZ4X': What were the four goals set during development? |author=塩谷公邦 |date=April 12, 2022 |work=Car Watch |access-date=3 May 2022}}</ref>

=== North America ===
The North American market-spec bZ4X was unveiled at the [[LA Auto Show#2021|2021 Los Angeles Auto Show]], with its specifications also detailed by that time, including its on-sale date set in mid-2022, for the 2023 model year.<ref>{{cite press release |url=https://pressroom.toyota.com/revealed-the-all-new-all-electric-toyota-bz4x/ |title=Revealed: The All-New, All-Electric Toyota bZ4X |publisher=Toyota |location=Australian |date=2021-11-17 |access-date=2021-12-28}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://insideevs.com/news/547749/toyota-bz4x-debuts-us/ |title=Toyota bZ4X Debuts In The U.S., Will Go On Sale Mid-2022 |first=Mark |last=Kane |work=InsideEvs |location=US |date=2021-11-17 |access-date=2021-12-28}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.greencarreports.com/news/1134196_2023-toyota-bz4x-ev-electric-suv-photos-specs-range-review-info |title=Preview: 2023 Toyota bZ4X EV confirmed for 250-mile estimated range, due in mid 2022 |first=Bengt |last=Halvorson |work=Green Car Reports |location=US |date=2021-11-17 |access-date=2021-12-28}}</ref> Toyota-estimated range for the front-wheel-drive XLE model is up to {{convert|250|miles|km|round=5|order=flip|abbr=in}}.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Gauthier|first=Michael|date=2021-11-17|title=First Look: 2023 Toyota bZ4X Electric Crossover Debuts In U.S., Offers Up To 250 Miles Range|url=https://www.carscoops.com/2021/11/first-look-the-2023-toyota-bz4x-spearheads-the-companys-electric-push-and-offers-up-to-250-miles-of-range/|url-status=live|access-date=2021-11-17|website=Carscoops|language=en-US|archive-date=30 November 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211130101854/https://www.carscoops.com/2021/11/first-look-the-2023-toyota-bz4x-spearheads-the-companys-electric-push-and-offers-up-to-250-miles-of-range/}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.theverge.com/2022/4/12/23022385/toyota-bz4x-ev-suv-pricing-availability-announcement |title=Toyota's bZ4X all-electric SUV will start at $42,000 |author=Clark, Mitchell |date=April 12, 2022 |work=The Verge |access-date=3 May 2022}}</ref>

At launch, American buyers qualify for the full {{USD|7500}} federal tax subsidy for purchasing an electric vehicle; each automobile manufacturer may sell up to 200,000 cars that qualify for the tax credit. Because Toyota plug-in hybrid vehicles also qualify for the tax credit, the credits are anticipated to be exhausted shortly after the launch of the bZ4X.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.cnn.com/2022/04/12/business/toyota-bz4x-review/index.html |title=Toyota finally has an EV and it's perfectly OK |last=Valdes-Dapena |first=Peter |date=April 12, 2022 |work=CNN Business |access-date=3 May 2022}}</ref> The bZ4X is not eligible for electric vehicle incentives from the [[Inflation Reduction Act of 2022|Inflation Reduction Act]] because it is made in Japan, not the US, Canada, or Mexico.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2023-01-24 |title=Toyota Stays Modest about EVs as It Relaunches bZ4X after Recall |url=https://www.caranddriver.com/news/a42624715/2023-toyota-bz4x-on-sale-relaunch/ |access-date=2023-03-01 |website=Car and Driver |language=en-us}}</ref>

=== Europe ===
Under the [[Worldwide Harmonised Light Vehicles Test Procedure|WLTP driving cycle]], the front-wheel drive bZ4X achieves a range of {{cvt|516|km}} (14.3&nbsp;kWh/100&nbsp;km consumption) and the all-wheel drive bZ4X {{cvt|470|km}} (15.8&nbsp;kWh/100&nbsp;km).<ref>{{cite news |url=https://paultan.org/2022/04/05/toyota-bzx4-electric-suv-gets-516-km-wltp-range/ |title=Toyota bZ4X electric SUV gets 516&nbsp;km WLTP range |first=Jonathan |last=Lee |work=paultan.org |location=Malaysia |date=2022-04-05 |access-date=2022-05-24}}</ref> Deliveries of the first vehicles are expected to commence in summer 2022.<ref>{{cite press release |url=https://newsroom.toyota.eu/all-new-electric-toyota-bz4x-ready-for-european-sales-launch/ |title=All-new, electric Toyota bZ4X ready for European sales launch |date=30 March 2022 |publisher=Toyota |location=Europe |access-date=3 May 2022}}</ref>

=== Southeast Asia ===
The bZ4X was first announced in Singapore by Borneo Motors (Toyota's authorised retailer in Singapore) in June 2022 as part of an electric car-sharing program in the country's [[Tengah, Singapore|Tengah New Town]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://carbuyer.com.sg/2022-toyota-bz4x-borneo-motors-sp-group-ev-car-sharing-tengah-singapore/|title=Borneo Motors and SP Group to develop EV sharing programme in Tengah|publisher=Car Buyer (Singapore)|date=June 30, 2022|accessdate=January 1, 2023}}</ref> Although the car-sharing program would be rolled out in June 2023, the car has not been made available for sale in the country.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.sgcarmart.com/news/article.php?AID=26945&CT=n|title=Toyota's bZ4X is coming to Singapore, and you won't need to buy it to drive it|publisher=Sgcarmart|date=June 30, 2022|accessdate=January 13, 2023}}</ref>

The bZ4X was first showcased in Indonesia at the [[Indonesia International Auto Show#2022|29th Gaikindo Indonesia International Auto Show]], and launched to the market on 10 November 2022.<ref>{{cite news |last=Lye |first=Gerard |date=2022-11-14 |title=2023 Toyota bZ4X in Indonesia – 71.4 kWh battery; up to 500 km EV range; FWD; 218 PS, 266 Nm; fr RM352k |work=paultan.org |location=Malaysia |url=https://paultan.org/2022/11/14/2023-toyota-bz4x-launched-in-indonesia/ |access-date=2022-12-02}}</ref> It is imported from Japan. It was one of the official VIP vehicles used at the [[2022 G20 Bali summit]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Nanda |first=Aprida Mega |date=2022-11-18 |title=Toyota Segera Jual Mobil Listrik bZ4X Bekas KTT G20 |trans-title=Toyota Immediately Sells Used BZ4X Electric Car G20 Summit |url=https://www.kompas.com/otomotif/read/2022/11/18/135238815/toyota-segera-jual-mobil-listrik-bz4x-bekas-ktt-g20 |access-date=2022-12-02 |website=Kompas.com |language=id}}</ref>

The bZ4X was launched in Thailand on 9 November 2022. As with Malaysia, it is also imported from Japan.<ref>{{cite news |last=Lye |first=Gerard |date=2022-11-14 |title=2023 Toyota bZ4X launched in Thailand – EV with 71.4 kWh battery, 411 km range, 218 PS, 337 Nm; fr RM235k |work=paultan.org |location=Malaysia |url=https://paultan.org/2022/11/14/2023-toyota-bz4x-launched-in-thailand/ |access-date=2022-12-02}}</ref>

=== Australasia ===
The bZ4X was planned to debut in Australia in 2021 but it was delayed. Imports from Japan are scheduled to begin in 2024 to Australia, New Zealand, and New Caledonia, with orders to be taken from late 2023. The bZ4X will be Toyota's first battery electric vehicle in the Australasian market.<ref>{{cite news |last=Stevens |first=Mike |date=9 February 2023 |title=2024 Toyota BZ4x review: First spin on Australian asphalt |work=WhichCar |publication-place=Australia |publisher=Wheels Media |url= https://www.whichcar.com.au/reviews/2024-toyota-bz4x-review-first-spin-on-australian-asphalt |access-date=6 September 2023 }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=2024 Toyota BZ4x electric SUV delayed to next year |last=Hickey |first=Jordan |date=30 August 2023 |work=WhichCar |publication-place=Australia |publisher=Wheels Media |url= https://www.whichcar.com.au/news/2024-toyota-bz4x-electric-suv-delayed |access-date=6 September 2023 }}</ref>

=== China ===
The Chinese market bZ4X was produced and marketed by two separate joint ventures, [[GAC Toyota]] and [[FAW Toyota]]. Introduced in October 2022, both versions are equipped with batteries produced by [[CATL]]. The capacity options were 50.3&nbsp;kWh and 66.7&nbsp;kWh with a [[China Light-Duty Vehicle Test Cycle|CLTC]] range of {{cvt|400|km}} and {{cvt|615|km}} respectively.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2022-10-12 |title=血拼到底，广汽丰田bZ4X以“全球最低价”上市 |trans-title=After fighting to the end, GAC Toyota bZ4X is launched at the “world’s lowest price” |url=https://www.sohu.com/a/592226147_115706 |access-date=2023-12-27 |website=www.sohu.com}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=2022-10-25 |title=一汽丰田bZ4X正式上市 售价19.98万元起{{!}}一汽丰田-网通社汽车 |trans-title=FAW Toyota bZ4X officially launched, priced from 199,800 yuan |url=https://auto.news18a.com/news/storys_165305.html |access-date=2023-12-27 |website=auto.news18a.com}}</ref>

After a series of price cuts due to slow sales,<ref>{{Cite web |last=快科技 |date=2023-02-09 |title=特斯拉降价丰田不装了！首款电动车bZ4X狂降3万：仅需16.98万起 |trans-title=Tesla cuts prices, Toyota stops installing them! The first electric car bZ4X is discounted by RMB 30,000: starting from only RMB 169,800 |url=https://finance.sina.com.cn/tech/roll/2023-02-09/doc-imyfamqw3047576.shtml |access-date=2023-12-27 |website=Sina Finance}}</ref> Toyota released an update for the bZ4X in November 2023. A four-wheel drive option became available, the 50.3&nbsp;kWh battery option was removed, and the exterior plastic body claddings are now body coloured. The vehicle received a Chinese name ({{zh|s=铂智4X|t=|p=Bózhì 4X|c=|l=Platinum 4X}}). The 'Bozhi' name will be the Chinese sub-brand for GAC Toyota’s electric vehicles, mirroring the bZ sub-brand globally. The FAW Toyota version was discontinued.<ref>{{Cite web |last=McDee |first=Max |date=2023-12-27 |title=Toyota unveils Bozhi 4X electric SUV in China |url=https://www.arenaev.com/toyota_unveils_bozhi_4x_electric_suv_in_china-news-2931.php |access-date=2023-12-27 |website=ArenaEV.com |language=en-US}}</ref>

