-electric-crossover-looks-just-like-the-toyota-bz4x/|url-status=live}}</ref> it uses the same e-TNGA platform rebranded to "e-Subaru Global Platform" (e-SGP).<ref>{{Cite web|title=Subaru Solterra due in 2022 as firm's first electric car|url=https://www.autocar.co.uk/car-news/new-cars/subaru-solterra-due-2022-firms-first-electric-car|access-date=2021-05-11|website=Autocar|language=en|archive-date=12 May 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210512190702/https://www.autocar.co.uk/car-news/new-cars/subaru-solterra-due-2022-firms-first-electric-car|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|date=2021-05-11|title=Subaru Solterra is the next Toyobaru project... and it's electric – Auto News|url=https://www.autoindustriya.com/auto-industry-news/subaru-solterra-is-the-next-toyobaru-project-and-it-s-electric.html|access-date=2021-05-11|website=AutoIndustriya.com|language=en|archive-date=12 May 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210512202411/https://www.autoindustriya.com/auto-industry-news/subaru-solterra-is-the-next-toyobaru-project-and-it-s-electric.html|url-status=live}}</ref> The Solterra went on sale in mid-2022 in Japan, US, Canada, Europe, and China.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Subaru Solterra Teased As Electric SUV Co-Developed With Toyota|url=https://www.motor1.com/news/506572/subaru-solterra-electric-suv-teaser/|access-date=2021-05-11|website=Motor1.com|language=en|archive-date=13 May 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210513161617/https://www.motor1.com/news/506572/subaru-solterra-electric-suv-teaser/|url-status=live}}</ref>

